<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2025-11-06-black-and-white.png" alt="brotherton chess problem" width="382" height="387" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-72075" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2025-11-06-black-and-white.png 382w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2025-11-06-black-and-white-300x304.png 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 382px) 100vw, 382px" /></p>
<p>With this problem D.W.A. Brotherton won second prize in a 1955 competition for British composers under 21. White to mate in two moves.</p>

